<Action id="24342" issue="15842" author="wlahti" type="comment" created="2017-05-25 15:48:00.0" updateauthor="wlahti" updated="2017-05-25 15:48:00.0"> <body><! CDATA Yes, as  ~hanwei  pointed out, a valid channel ID cannot contain an underscore. Here are the code comments for the validateChainID function:  {code:java} // validateChainID makes sure that proposed chain IDs (i.e. channel names) // comply with the following restrictions: // 1. Contain only ASCII alphanumerics, dots '.', dashes '-' // 2. Are shorter than 250 characters. // 3. Are not the strings "." or "..". // // Our hand here is forced by: // https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/common/Topic.scala#L29{code}       ></body> </Action>
